1
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:34,900
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,190 --> 00:01:37,759
[Episode 4]

3
00:01:38,229 --> 00:01:41,150
The East Chemical Plant
anniversary celebration is coming up!

4
00:01:41,150 --> 00:01:44,350
Starring superstar Zhuang Sen
and Zhang Xiaoman!

5
00:01:44,350 --> 00:01:45,710
Just hand them out. Don't shout, okay?

6
00:01:45,710 --> 00:01:46,710
Why can't I shout?

7
00:01:47,039 --> 00:01:48,570
Come and show some support.

8
00:01:48,590 --> 00:01:49,390
No, I'll pass.

9
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:50,950
-Come and watch the show.
-Come on, quit fronting.

10
00:01:50,950 --> 00:01:51,950
-Anniversary celebration.
-Come on.

11
00:01:51,950 --> 00:01:52,710
The factory's anniversary celebration.
Come on, check it out.

12
00:01:52,710 --> 00:01:53,200
Come watch the show.

13
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:53,920
Anniversary celebration.
Come watch the show.

14
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:54,590
Anniversary celebration. It's for free.

15
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:55,870
Row 21? But I wanted the front row.

16
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:57,400
Come on, anniversary celebration.
Want to watch?

17
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,710
-Forget it.
-Anniversary celebration tickets.

18
00:01:58,710 --> 00:01:59,840
Xiaoman and I are performing.
Check it out.

19
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:00,430
Xiaoman?

20
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:01,050
Tickets.

21
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:02,480
Tickets for the anniversary celebration.
Want to watch?

22
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,530
Here, anniversary celebration tickets.

23
00:02:03,530 --> 00:02:04,400
Come check it out.

24
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,060
Xiaoman and I are performing.

25
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,750
No thanks. We've already got ours.

26
00:02:08,750 --> 00:02:09,870
Come here, bro.

27
00:02:09,870 --> 00:02:10,400
What for?

28
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:11,160
I'll pass.

29
00:02:11,470 --> 00:02:12,030
Take one.

30
00:02:12,030 --> 00:02:12,630
Hot off the press, huh?

31
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:13,760
You're hopeless.

32
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:15,790
Who can hear you whispering like that?

33
00:02:15,790 --> 00:02:17,120
Alright, I'll take one.

34
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,280
Hey guys!

35
00:02:18,630 --> 00:02:19,520
Our factory's anniversary celebration
is coming up.

36
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:22,800
Zhuang Sen and Xiaoman are performing.
Make sure to come and support them.

37
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:23,910
D-Do you have front row tickets?

38
00:02:23,910 --> 00:02:25,400
Sure, let me look. Here.

39
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:27,680
-Alright, alright.
-Good for you.

40
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,560
Come on. T-Take two.

41
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,540
Anniversary celebration tickets.

42
00:02:31,540 --> 00:02:32,000
Here, take it.

43
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,190
Pulling something this big off
without saying a word, huh?

44
00:02:33,190 --> 00:02:34,250
You bet. Take this.

45
00:02:35,030 --> 00:02:35,630
Well,

46
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:36,890
I want one more.

47
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,579
Who are you taking?

48
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,050
Not sure yet.

49
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,030
You'd better bring someone, okay?

50
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:43,520
These tickets are in high demand,
you know?

51
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:44,430
Don't let it go to waste.

52
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:45,750
I'll try my best. I will.

53
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:46,560
I'm going home now.

54
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:47,630
-Alright.
-We're off.

55
00:02:47,630 --> 00:02:48,630
What are you talking about, fake tickets?
They're real.

56
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:49,120
Remember to come.

57
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,380
Guys, guys, over here.

58
00:02:50,630 --> 00:02:51,520
8-8:00 PM.

59
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:52,430
Meng Ge. Meng Ge.

60
00:02:52,430 --> 00:02:54,310
Here. Zhuang Sen and Xiaoman
are performing.

61
00:02:54,310 --> 00:02:55,030
You've got to come.

62
00:02:55,030 --> 00:02:56,360
I'll take one for Sun Lulu.

63
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:58,000
No, you've got to come as well, okay?

64
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:58,630
Alright, alright.

65
00:02:58,630 --> 00:02:59,310
Give me one.

66
00:02:59,310 --> 00:03:00,110
I'll take two.

67
00:03:02,270 --> 00:03:04,190
Your girlfriend really came through.

68
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:05,050
What time is it?

69
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,030
What girlfriend?

70
00:03:06,030 --> 00:03:08,030
S-She's the host for
our anniversary celebration.

71
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:11,160
Three tickets. You three
have got to come and support us.

72
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:12,210
Xiaodan.

73
00:03:12,950 --> 00:03:14,350
Xiaodan! Xiaodan!

74
00:03:15,510 --> 00:03:16,910
Thanks for your hard work.

75
00:03:16,910 --> 00:03:17,910
It's nothing.

76
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:19,840
Our factory's anniversary celebration
is coming up.

77
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:22,040
Zhuang Sen and Xiaoman are performing.

78
00:03:22,190 --> 00:03:23,430
Anniversary celebration tickets...

79
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:24,890
I've got a brilliant idea.

80
00:03:25,190 --> 00:03:26,190
If this works out,

81
00:03:26,430 --> 00:03:28,329
we'll make a big name for ourselves
at the East Chemical Plant.

82
00:03:28,329 --> 00:03:30,030
Grandma will walk around like
she owns the place after seeing the show.

83
00:03:30,030 --> 00:03:31,190
Zhuang Sen and Xiaoman are performing.

84
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:33,200
-You've got to come and watch.
-What is it?

85
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:34,150
-Mr. Ding.
-Mrs. Ding.

86
00:03:34,150 --> 00:03:35,120
Come on, show us your tickets.

87
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:36,280
Tickets, please. Come on.

88
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:37,079
Here, take this.

89
00:03:37,079 --> 00:03:38,310
Go on in.

90
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,300
-See you later.
-Alright.

91
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:41,120
You're here so early.

92
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,360
Look at all that sweat.

93
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:42,680
Go on in.

94
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:43,840
Come on, quick! Uncles and Aunties, hurry!

95
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:45,630
Hurry up and get on stage. Quick, quick.

96
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:46,150
Come on.

97
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:48,690
Quick, get the children down. Hurry.

98
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,030
Be careful. Come on.

99
00:03:51,030 --> 00:03:52,160
Follow the teacher.

100
00:03:52,630 --> 00:03:53,680
Eyes forward.

101
00:03:54,030 --> 00:03:55,160
Let's stand by here.

102
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:57,000
Come on.

103
00:03:57,870 --> 00:03:59,030
Fourth Sister-in-law, you look beautiful.

104
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,470
Check out that outfit. You're really
getting prettier and prettier.

105
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:01,520
Cut it out.

106
00:04:05,030 --> 00:04:06,160
Stay calm, alright?

107
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:08,460
Stay calm.

108
00:04:08,490 --> 00:04:09,440
I know, I know.

109
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:11,710
Just wait quietly for that moment.

110
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,080
Here you are.

111
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:13,630
You're here.

112
00:04:13,630 --> 00:04:14,190
You're here.

113
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:14,960
Quite early.

114
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:16,600
Here, over here.

115
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:18,269
Come on, sit down.

116
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:23,260
[East Integrated Chemical Plant
30th Anniversary Gala]

117
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,390
He's a model worker, after all.

118
00:04:20,390 --> 00:04:21,269
Come on, stop teasing me.

119
00:04:21,269 --> 00:04:22,070
Is this the second row?

120
00:04:22,070 --> 00:04:23,530
Yes, it is. The second row.

121
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:27,760
The anniversary celebration is getting
less and less festive.

122
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:29,270
Even a few firecrackers

123
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,780
would liven things up a bit.

124
00:04:30,780 --> 00:04:32,490
It's good enough
that we're still doing it.

125
00:04:32,490 --> 00:04:33,120
Isn't it?

126
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,360
Firecrackers would cost extra.

127
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,690
Haven't you seen the state of our factory?

128
00:04:38,030 --> 00:04:40,590
How much could that possibly cost?

129
00:04:41,390 --> 00:04:43,870
If we don't build up the morale,

130
00:04:43,870 --> 00:04:45,420
we're bound to lose, you know?

131
00:04:45,420 --> 00:04:46,780
Keep it down.

132
00:04:48,190 --> 00:04:49,720
It's good enough
that we're still doing it.

133
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:52,050
It shows our factory hasn't gone bust yet.

134
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:55,500
This lone garlic here's still got
30 more years of spice left.

135
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:57,100
It's barely been a few years.

136
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:20,360
Nervous?

137
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:21,630
Why would we be nervous?

138
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:23,240
No, we're just excited.

139
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:24,430
Excitement is good.

140
00:05:24,430 --> 00:05:25,600
Make sure to be pumped
when you get on stage.

141
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,040
Got it.

142
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,630
By the great rivers,

143
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:46,480
we set sail for the future!

144
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:50,870
The low hum of machines
echoes through the valley.

145
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:53,920
That's a huge turnout.

146
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:57,360
It is the song of creation
for generations of Donghua people!

147
00:05:58,270 --> 00:06:01,530
-We create miracles here.
-Why hasn't my grandma arrived?

148
00:06:01,830 --> 00:06:02,690
She must've got

149
00:06:03,390 --> 00:06:05,680
-held up on the way.
-East Chemical Plant,

150
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,840
-It's okay. I'm sure she'll come.
-I'm proud of you!

151
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:08,840
Come on, let's go.

152
00:06:09,390 --> 00:06:13,310
I'm honored to be part of you!

153
00:06:14,310 --> 00:06:16,560
Donghua people united,

154
00:06:17,070 --> 00:06:20,360
forging the glory of our motherland!

155
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:22,800
Bravo!

156
00:06:23,660 --> 00:06:28,300
Bravo! Bravo!

157
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,560
Thank you for the thunderous applause.

158
00:06:31,630 --> 00:06:32,830
Coming up next

159
00:06:32,830 --> 00:06:33,680
is a guitar sing-along

160
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:36,830
by Zhang Xiaoman and Zhuang Sen

161
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:38,480
from Dongfang Affiliated Middle School,

162
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:40,070
performing

163
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:42,120
"We Workers Have The Power."

164
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:44,390
Great!

165
00:06:46,270 --> 00:06:47,720
Go, Zhang Xiaoman!

166
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:48,800
Go, Xiaoman!

167
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:54,000
Everyone's really backing Xiaoman.

168
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:54,510
Yeah.

169
00:07:00,380 --> 00:07:02,260
♪ We workers have the power ♪

170
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:05,950
♪ Busy at work every day ♪

171
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:10,490
The lights are out.

172
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,360
The fuse must have blown.

173
00:07:14,950 --> 00:07:16,070
What kind of setup is this?

174
00:07:16,070 --> 00:07:17,670
They've only sung two lines.

175
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,210
Why did they stop singing?

176
00:07:20,430 --> 00:07:21,830
Why did the lights go out?

177
00:07:22,070 --> 00:07:24,270
Well, the youngsters

178
00:07:24,430 --> 00:07:26,430
are probably
experimenting with something new.

179
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:28,290
Keeping up with the times, right?

180
00:07:37,980 --> 00:07:40,100
-So cool, Xiaoman!
-Xiaoman!

181
00:07:55,270 --> 00:07:56,130
Look, the kids.

182
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:12,720
♪ A pair of hands
that can no longer be beautified ♪

183
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:15,870
♪ Yet envelops with warmth ♪

184
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:18,430
♪ The constant nagging and care ♪

185
00:08:18,430 --> 00:08:20,870
♪ So guilty that I didn't cherish it ♪

186
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:25,390
♪ She didn't approve of me
being immersed in the music scene ♪

187
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:28,430
♪ But a mother's love never wanes ♪

188
00:08:28,870 --> 00:08:30,870
♪ Determined to break free from
the struggle within myself ♪

189
00:08:30,870 --> 00:08:33,390
♪ To finally repay
your love and kindness ♪

190
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:37,600
♪ As the warm spring gives way to rain,
your love warms my heart ♪

191
00:08:37,909 --> 00:08:42,220
♪ All my life you looked after me
without words ♪

192
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,360
Xiaoman, you're so cool!

193
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:45,390
♪ It is your warm gaze ♪

194
00:08:46,030 --> 00:08:48,600
♪ That teaches me to persevere
and focus on the road ahead ♪

195
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:54,400
♪ Reminding me not to give up
even when I fall ♪

196
00:08:53,510 --> 00:08:54,240
Come on, let's go.

197
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,000
Come on, let's go. Hurry!

198
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,840
♪ There's no way to explain
how repay your love ♪

199
00:08:58,360 --> 00:09:01,080
♪ Your love is vast and infinite ♪

200
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:06,870
♪ Please allow me to say
I really love you ♪

201
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:29,550
Xiaoman! Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

202
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:30,390
Stop dancing!

203
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:36,560
Get down here!

204
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:37,920
What's happening?

205
00:09:41,150 --> 00:09:41,870
Xiaoman!

206
00:09:41,870 --> 00:09:42,800
What's going on?

207
00:09:48,670 --> 00:09:49,320
I can walk.

208
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,190
Move. Come on.

209
00:09:50,210 --> 00:09:51,240
C-Can't I watch for a while?

210
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:51,960
Easy, okay?

211
00:09:53,410 --> 00:09:54,120
Get out.

212
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,600
C-Can't I just watch for a bit?

213
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,200
What's there to watch?

214
00:09:58,600 --> 00:09:59,600
Take these.

215
00:10:00,130 --> 00:10:01,350
Hurry up and leave. Close the door.

216
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:03,350
You really don't understand anything!

217
00:10:03,350 --> 00:10:04,010
Seriously.

218
00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:06,530
Unbelievable.

219
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:11,900
This is just great.

220
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,670
Dirty clothes.

221
00:10:15,390 --> 00:10:16,600
Nothing left.

222
00:10:18,630 --> 00:10:19,910
Don't lose heart, Xiaoman.

223
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:21,630
The birth of new things

224
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:23,040
is often questioned.

225
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,840
To light up the darkness before dawn

226
00:10:25,870 --> 00:10:26,910
takes courage.

227
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:30,420
Don't you think I'm a poet?

228
00:10:30,420 --> 00:10:31,520
I even rhymed.

229
00:10:35,220 --> 00:10:35,840
What's wrong?

230
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,440
We worked on this for so long.

231
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,440
I just wanted my grandma

232
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,120
to see me sing here.

233
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,380
Why is it so hard, huh?

234
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,500
Well, that's easy.

235
00:10:44,550 --> 00:10:45,790
I'll go home with you
and sing for your grandma.

236
00:10:45,790 --> 00:10:47,300
We can sing it as many times as you want.

237
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:48,820
How can that be the same?

238
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:49,960
Here we've got a stage,

239
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:51,840
music, lights, everything.

240
00:10:52,270 --> 00:10:54,390
And an audience cheering for us.

241
00:10:54,510 --> 00:10:56,390
Singing at home isn't even close.

242
00:10:58,560 --> 00:11:00,160
Get our classmates at your place,

243
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,760
and I'll play the accompaniment
for you again.

244
00:11:03,470 --> 00:11:04,270
Where is my grandma?

245
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:05,530
Why isn't she here yet?

246
00:11:06,790 --> 00:11:08,240
-Right.
-Could she have forgotten?

247
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:08,630
She couldn't have.

248
00:11:08,630 --> 00:11:10,560
I told her about this so many times.

249
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:11,970
I'll go home and check.

250
00:11:11,970 --> 00:11:12,970
Come on, let's go.

251
00:11:24,230 --> 00:11:25,030
Grandma.

252
00:11:27,090 --> 00:11:27,730
Grandma?

253
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:31,100
Where could she have gone?

254
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:41,480
Grandma? Where are you?

255
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,670
Look at this. The show is over.

256
00:11:57,270 --> 00:11:58,000
Grandma.

257
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:01,290
Grandma?

258
00:12:12,590 --> 00:12:13,850
You've finished watching the show, Uncle?

259
00:12:13,850 --> 00:12:14,490
Xiaoman.

260
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,160
What's going on here?

261
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:18,810
What are you looking at?

262
00:12:18,910 --> 00:12:19,650
It's nothing.

263
00:12:19,650 --> 00:12:20,320
It's nothing.

264
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:21,320
What do you mean, nothing?

265
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:22,150
What happened?

266
00:12:22,150 --> 00:12:23,220
Take it easy, alright?

267
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:23,670
What are you looking at?

268
00:12:23,670 --> 00:12:25,000
Come on, let us through.

269
00:12:25,340 --> 00:12:25,870
Xiaoman.

270
00:12:25,890 --> 00:12:27,070
Why is my grandma here?

271
00:12:27,070 --> 00:12:27,950
Xiaoman...

272
00:12:28,260 --> 00:12:29,060
Xiaoman...

273
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:31,690
It's okay, Xiaoman.

274
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,410
We're all here with you.

275
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:35,280
Take a look at your grandma.

276
00:12:37,890 --> 00:12:38,600
Grandma.

277
00:12:39,750 --> 00:12:40,440
Grandma.

278
00:12:52,090 --> 00:12:53,270
Grandma, let's go... Let's go home.

279
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:55,130
What are you doing here, Grandma?

280
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:55,890
Grandma?

281
00:12:58,370 --> 00:13:00,030
What... What happened to her?

282
00:13:01,190 --> 00:13:01,670
This...

283
00:13:03,870 --> 00:13:05,070
Your grandma is gone.

284
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:06,850
That's impossible. She just came out...

285
00:13:06,850 --> 00:13:08,780
She just came out to watch the show.

286
00:13:10,390 --> 00:13:11,240
How could she...

287
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:11,790
Grandma.

288
00:13:12,170 --> 00:13:12,720
Grandma.

289
00:13:16,460 --> 00:13:17,080
Grandma, let's go home.

290
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:18,000
The sweater isn't finished yet.

291
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:18,690
Let's go. Let's go.

292
00:13:18,690 --> 00:13:19,220
Grandma.

293
00:13:20,390 --> 00:13:21,320
The sweater is only half done.

294
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:23,120
I haven't had a chance to wear it.

295
00:13:27,250 --> 00:13:28,360
Xiaoman...

296
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:31,490
We can go home.

297
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:32,850
Grandma, let's go home.

298
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,680
-Xiaoman, don't…
-Grandma.

299
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:37,200
She can't go home with you anymore.

300
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:43,510
Xiaoman.

301
00:13:44,230 --> 00:13:46,090
Pull yourself together. Come on.

302
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:47,300
Let's...

303
00:13:48,270 --> 00:13:49,350
Everyone, please help.

304
00:13:49,350 --> 00:13:50,390
Let's get Grandma home.

305
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:51,390
Give us a hand. Come on.

306
00:13:51,390 --> 00:13:52,320
Xiaoman. Xiaoman.

307
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:53,580
You're a grown man now.

308
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:54,720
Get up first.

309
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:55,540
Your grandma...

310
00:13:55,540 --> 00:13:56,330
Xiaoman.

311
00:13:57,150 --> 00:13:58,750
-She didn't suffer.
-Listen to me, Xiaoman.

312
00:13:58,750 --> 00:14:00,960
C-Can you just listen to me?

313
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:01,670
Xiaoman.

314
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:06,200
Grandma didn't suffer, alright?

315
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:07,250
Come on, get up.

316
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:09,200
Come on. Let's take Grandma home.

317
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,130
Get up, Xiaoman.

318
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,000
Be good. Be good, Xiaoman.

319
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:12,510
Come on.

320
00:14:12,630 --> 00:14:13,390
Be good.

321
00:14:13,790 --> 00:14:14,250
Come on.

322
00:14:14,510 --> 00:14:15,550
Come on, everyone, give us a hand.

323
00:14:15,550 --> 00:14:16,390
Help us hold her. Come on.

324
00:14:16,390 --> 00:14:18,320
We can't let Grandma just sit here.

325
00:14:18,630 --> 00:14:19,200
Come on.

326
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:20,020
Lend a hand.

327
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:21,360
We're all here. We're all here.

328
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:21,790
Let's go.

329
00:14:21,790 --> 00:14:23,010
-Easy.
-We're all here.

330
00:14:23,010 --> 00:14:23,560
Come on.

331
00:14:27,790 --> 00:14:28,600
Easy.

332
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:31,840
Careful. Easy, easy.

333
00:14:34,090 --> 00:14:34,960
Get over here!

334
00:14:35,350 --> 00:14:36,650
Are you a delinquent, too?

335
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:38,370
Do you want me, at my age,

336
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:40,130
to bail you out of jail someday?

337
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:41,510
It's not like that.

338
00:14:41,510 --> 00:14:43,510
Grandma, d-don't be mad.

339
00:14:43,510 --> 00:14:44,360
Don't listen to their nonsense.

340
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:46,420
I won't do it again. I know I was wrong.

341
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:48,840
Grandma!

342
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,000
Don't leave me!

343
00:14:50,270 --> 00:14:51,000
Grandma!

344
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,920
-Xiaoman!
-Xiaoman!

345
00:14:52,940 --> 00:14:53,470
Grandma!

346
00:14:53,620 --> 00:14:54,640
What are you doing, Xiaoman?

347
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:55,240
Grandma!

348
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:57,360
Don't be like this, Xiaoman.

349
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:58,120
Xiaoman.

350
00:14:58,790 --> 00:14:59,360
Xiaoman.

351
00:15:00,630 --> 00:15:01,480
Xiaoman.

352
00:15:01,550 --> 00:15:03,390
-Xiaoman.
-Xiaoman, be good!

353
00:15:03,390 --> 00:15:04,550
Let's take Grandma home first.

354
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:05,750
Xiaoman, be good.

355
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:06,510
Xiaoman, no matter how hard you cry,

356
00:15:06,510 --> 00:15:07,960
don't let your tears
fall on Grandma's face,

357
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:08,670
you know?

358
00:15:08,870 --> 00:15:10,360
Or she won't be able to rest in peace.

359
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:11,150
You know?

360
00:15:11,970 --> 00:15:13,810
Don't take her away. Don't.

361
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:17,080
-Xiaoman!
-Xiaoman!

362
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:19,200
Let Grandma go!

363
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:21,750
Grandma.

364
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:22,600
Grandma...

365
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:23,370
Be good.

366
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:24,600
Hold him back.

367
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:25,930
Grandma... Grandma...

368
00:15:27,270 --> 00:15:27,930
Grandma...

369
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:30,120
-Xiaoman...
-Grandma is going home.

370
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:31,670
-Xiaoman, don't...
-Xiaoman!

371
00:15:31,670 --> 00:15:32,360
Don't go over there!

372
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:34,150
Xiaoman!

373
00:15:34,150 --> 00:15:35,480
Come back, Xiaoman!

374
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:36,510
Xiaoman...

375
00:15:41,060 --> 00:15:41,720
Xiaoman!

376
00:15:43,180 --> 00:15:43,780
Xiaoman.

377
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:45,400
Grandma... Grandma...

378
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:46,510
L-Let's go home.

379
00:15:46,510 --> 00:15:47,200
Xiaoman.

380
00:15:47,220 --> 00:15:48,580
Grandma, let's go home.

381
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:50,870
-Grandma.
-Come on. Push.

382
00:15:50,870 --> 00:15:51,630
Let Xiaoman push. Come on.

383
00:15:51,630 --> 00:15:53,270
Grandma... Grandma...

384
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:54,910
Let's go home.

385
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:06,150
You,

386
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:08,110
just bless our grandson

387
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:12,840
to have a steady and safe life, alright?

388
00:16:51,860 --> 00:16:57,010
♪ Outside the walls,
the west wind rises, smoke drifts ♪

389
00:16:57,200 --> 00:17:01,440
♪ Lanterns sway gently ♪

390
00:17:02,580 --> 00:17:07,660
♪ Cicadas sing tirelessly in the dusk ♪

391
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:11,640
♪ The young run swiftly, without rest ♪

392
00:17:13,470 --> 00:17:18,819
♪ Time stretches long,
people travel 1,000 miles ♪

393
00:17:18,839 --> 00:17:22,619
♪ Looking back, the mountains are gone ♪

394
00:17:23,710 --> 00:17:28,940
♪ Parting now,
the road to the horizon stretches on ♪

395
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:33,350
♪ Plum blossoms bloom again,
another year passes ♪

396
00:17:56,050 --> 00:18:01,450
♪ Time stretches long,
people travel 1,000 miles ♪

397
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:05,240
♪ Looking back, the mountains are gone ♪

398
00:18:06,430 --> 00:18:11,620
♪ Parting now,
the road to the horizon stretches on ♪

399
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:16,300
♪ Plum blossoms bloom again,
another year passes ♪

400
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:22,530
♪ Voices echo from the past ♪

401
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:28,040
♪ In the neighborhood,
whose playful child races under the sun? ♪

402
00:18:28,090 --> 00:18:33,250
♪ Whispering your name, can you hear it? ♪

403
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:37,210
♪ Evening song plays ♪

404
00:18:38,570 --> 00:18:43,800
♪ People gone, leaving only a lone shadow
in the setting sun ♪

405
00:18:43,980 --> 00:18:48,580
♪ Sighing, where is home? ♪

406
00:19:04,940 --> 00:19:07,380
Dad, you're so cruel.

407
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:09,320
Grandma's gone,

408
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:12,150
and you didn't even come back
to bid her farewell.

409
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:22,800
[East Integrated Chemical Plant]

410
00:19:23,590 --> 00:19:25,960
Ding, it's really great that you want

411
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:27,140
to be Xiaoman's guardian.

412
00:19:27,140 --> 00:19:28,200
You don't know yet—

413
00:19:28,220 --> 00:19:31,480
Jiaming had an accident in the south,
and he didn't make it.

414
00:19:33,510 --> 00:19:35,200
I didn't know how to break it to him,

415
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:37,130
and now Xiaoman's grandma also...

416
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:39,280
Why did it all happen at once?

417
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:46,070
It's just that I still need to
handle some paperwork here.

418
00:19:46,070 --> 00:19:48,270
You go back and get the documents ready.

419
00:19:48,310 --> 00:19:49,510
Proceed with it then.

420
00:19:50,110 --> 00:19:51,440
Director Liu, Mr. Ding.

421
00:19:51,490 --> 00:19:52,100
Xiaoman.

422
00:19:52,990 --> 00:19:55,120
Well, my grandma

423
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:57,030
sewed some small cushions
for our factory.

424
00:19:57,030 --> 00:19:58,250
They just filled up a box,

425
00:19:58,250 --> 00:19:59,510
so I brought them over.

426
00:20:02,190 --> 00:20:03,120
Ding.

427
00:20:03,430 --> 00:20:05,230
Comrade He Yuexiang's grandson

428
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:06,540
is our family, too.

429
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:11,670
Xiaoman, have your meals at the cafeteria
from now on.

430
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:12,900
Go whenever you like.

431
00:20:13,910 --> 00:20:16,350
As for your daily expenses,

432
00:20:17,100 --> 00:20:18,640
go to the finance office every month

433
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:20,500
to collect a 100-yuan allowance.

434
00:20:21,360 --> 00:20:22,720
Thank you, Director Liu.

435
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:23,720
Don't mention it.

436
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:25,430
You know,

437
00:20:26,110 --> 00:20:27,160
your grandparents

438
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:30,090
were both first-generation workers
of our factory,

439
00:20:30,090 --> 00:20:31,690
and they left us so suddenly.

440
00:20:32,350 --> 00:20:34,440
Don't think about your father.

441
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:36,810
He's out there and can't come back.

442
00:20:36,920 --> 00:20:37,750
Also,

443
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:40,240
Mr. Ding here wants to be your guardian.

444
00:20:40,590 --> 00:20:41,960
As for the paperwork,

445
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:43,360
it needs to be processed.

446
00:20:43,780 --> 00:20:45,750
You can still collect the money yourself.

447
00:20:45,750 --> 00:20:46,610
When you do,

448
00:20:46,630 --> 00:20:48,290
keep a record of your spending

449
00:20:48,550 --> 00:20:50,480
and remember to show it to Mr. Ding.

450
00:20:51,070 --> 00:20:53,550
It's not that
I want to control your spending.

451
00:20:53,550 --> 00:20:53,960
Right.

452
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:55,440
You're young,

453
00:20:55,540 --> 00:20:56,510
and you haven't seen
this much money before.

454
00:20:56,510 --> 00:20:57,920
I'm worried you might spend it recklessly.

455
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:59,790
Once you know how to manage it,
I won't interfere.

456
00:20:59,790 --> 00:21:00,360
Okay.

457
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:02,240
And one more thing.

458
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,360
About the cafeteria,

459
00:21:05,510 --> 00:21:07,240
eat there if you want, or don't.

460
00:21:07,950 --> 00:21:09,350
Just come eat at my place.

461
00:21:10,660 --> 00:21:12,620
If your aunt and I are too busy to cook,

462
00:21:12,620 --> 00:21:14,220
then go eat at the cafeteria.

463
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:15,880
Thank you, Mr. Ding.

464
00:21:31,710 --> 00:21:32,310
He's here.

465
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:33,560
He's here.

466
00:21:35,310 --> 00:21:36,240
He's here. He's here.

467
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:37,100
He's here, huh?

468
00:21:51,270 --> 00:21:52,460
Yeah, he's coming up the stairs.

469
00:21:52,460 --> 00:21:53,460
Okay, wait there.

470
00:21:56,550 --> 00:21:57,350
Xiaoman.

471
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,110
You're here.

472
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:01,070
Come on.

473
00:22:01,250 --> 00:22:02,660
Wipe your hands and face.

474
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:06,090
Smell this. Doesn't it smell good?

475
00:22:07,250 --> 00:22:07,860
Mr. Ding.

476
00:22:07,890 --> 00:22:08,960
Come on in.

477
00:22:09,550 --> 00:22:11,410
Come on in. You, go peel a tangerine
and open a soda for him.

478
00:22:11,410 --> 00:22:12,400
I don't need help here. Go.

479
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,070
Come on in, Xiaoman.

480
00:22:13,070 --> 00:22:13,550
Come on in.

481
00:22:13,550 --> 00:22:14,030
Look at...

482
00:22:14,030 --> 00:22:15,960
Look at him tossing the wok.

483
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:16,440
It'll be ready soon.

484
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:17,510
You... Go inside.

485
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:21,050
Have some water.

486
00:22:21,050 --> 00:22:21,580
Okay.

487
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:22,600
Tangerines!

488
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:23,670
Peel a tangerine.

489
00:22:24,110 --> 00:22:24,720
Pick a big one.

490
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:25,680
That one on top is good.

491
00:22:25,680 --> 00:22:26,510
Got it.

492
00:22:27,630 --> 00:22:28,790
-Let me peel it for you.
-I'll peel it myself.

493
00:22:28,790 --> 00:22:29,830
D-Don't worry about me.

494
00:22:29,830 --> 00:22:31,160
I'm fine. Don't mind me.

495
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:32,790
Have some water then.

496
00:22:32,790 --> 00:22:33,310
Okay.

497
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:36,140
I'll go help him.

498
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:36,830
Alright.

499
00:22:36,830 --> 00:22:37,400
Where's the plate?

500
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:38,440
Coming, coming. The plate?

501
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,550
Here. Isn't it right here?

502
00:22:39,550 --> 00:22:40,920
-Come on.
-I've washed it for you.

503
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:41,810
Isn't it right here?

504
00:22:41,810 --> 00:22:42,680
You should've put it down earlier.

505
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:44,380
Next time, put it right in front of me.

506
00:22:44,380 --> 00:22:45,350
Alright, alright, right in front of you.

507
00:22:45,350 --> 00:22:46,680
So I don't have to look for it, you know?

508
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:47,240
Here.

509
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:47,960
Come on.

510
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:48,590
Let's eat.

511
00:22:48,590 --> 00:22:49,160
Let's eat.

512
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:49,750
Put this away.

513
00:22:49,750 --> 00:22:52,010
We should stop wearing this
when we cook.

514
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:53,400
Don't stand on ceremony.
Give him a pair of chopsticks.

515
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,460
Come on, let's eat.

516
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:55,960
Here.

517
00:22:56,410 --> 00:22:57,140
Here you are.

518
00:22:58,310 --> 00:23:00,160
What's wrong? Not to your liking?

519
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:00,960
No, it's fine.

520
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:02,270
-Give him a bit extra. He's a big guy.
-Okay.

521
00:23:02,270 --> 00:23:03,110
Pile it high.

522
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:07,360
That's enough.

523
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:07,750
Enough?

524
00:23:07,750 --> 00:23:08,240
Yeah.

525
00:23:08,470 --> 00:23:10,870
-Eat more.
-Refill once he's done. Come on.

526
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:13,010
Taste it. See if you like it.

527
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:14,910
Go easy on the alcohol.

528
00:23:14,910 --> 00:23:16,590
You both eat more meat.

529
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:18,600
Here. Have a balanced diet.

530
00:23:19,310 --> 00:23:20,920
I'm not fond of big chunks of meat.

531
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:21,980
Bones are tastier.

532
00:23:22,390 --> 00:23:23,790
He bought you this soda.

533
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,460
-Drink some.
-Come on.

534
00:23:25,830 --> 00:23:26,720
Eat plenty,

535
00:23:27,310 --> 00:23:28,270
grow strong.

536
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:30,350
Fill it up,

537
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,510
grow tall.

538
00:23:32,510 --> 00:23:33,970
Yours doesn't make sense.

539
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:35,590
You want some too?

540
00:23:35,590 --> 00:23:36,110
No.

541
00:23:36,310 --> 00:23:37,070
No?

542
00:23:38,470 --> 00:23:40,070
Let me fill it up for Xiaoman.

543
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:46,720
Go get some tissues.

544
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:51,490
Eat up. Stop overthinking.

545
00:23:52,580 --> 00:23:53,980
Everyone has their time.

546
00:23:58,020 --> 00:23:59,750
Have some of that dish. Come on.

547
00:24:00,340 --> 00:24:01,340
Be good, alright?

548
00:24:02,310 --> 00:24:02,920
Towel.

549
00:24:15,490 --> 00:24:16,010
Eat up.

550
00:24:16,800 --> 00:24:18,310
Xiaoman, as long as you live well,

551
00:24:18,310 --> 00:24:19,940
Grandma will be at peace in Heaven.

552
00:24:19,940 --> 00:24:21,490
We're both here with you.

553
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,300
I went to Mr. Ding's for dinner.

554
00:24:46,300 --> 00:24:48,430
He gave me some extra food to take home.

555
00:25:28,350 --> 00:25:29,070
Xiaoman.

556
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:43,720
Auntie.

557
00:25:44,870 --> 00:25:46,930
You'll catch a cold if you sleep here.

558
00:25:47,510 --> 00:25:49,840
It's okay. I'm just napping here
for a bit.

559
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:54,640
Want to rest a bit longer?

560
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:55,680
No, I'm good.

561
00:25:57,090 --> 00:25:57,990
What do you want to eat?

562
00:25:57,990 --> 00:26:00,070
I'll go make you something warm.

563
00:26:02,360 --> 00:26:03,220
I'm not hungry.

564
00:26:04,460 --> 00:26:05,800
Did Grandma knit this?

565
00:26:09,790 --> 00:26:11,270
Yeah, it's too big.

566
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:12,840
She only finished half of it.

567
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:15,380
She said I'd be able to wear it
next year...

568
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:20,570
I'll knit it for you.

569
00:26:20,830 --> 00:26:22,760
You'll be able to wear it this year.

570
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:26,030
G-Go lie down for a bit.

571
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:28,780
I'll go make you something delicious.

572
00:26:28,780 --> 00:26:29,640
Go on.

573
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:42,640
Auntie,

574
00:26:43,530 --> 00:26:44,680
rest assured.

575
00:26:45,590 --> 00:26:46,590
We're all here.

576
00:26:47,050 --> 00:26:48,280
We'll make sure to

577
00:26:48,310 --> 00:26:49,770
take good care of Xiaoman.

578
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:26,740
Xiaodan, what are you doing here?

579
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:28,330
Come on in.

580
00:27:29,230 --> 00:27:30,600
I wanted to check on you.

581
00:27:30,620 --> 00:27:32,680
My mom asked me to bring you some food.

582
00:27:36,570 --> 00:27:38,100
Come on, sit. Don't bother.

583
00:27:38,670 --> 00:27:40,200
Let me see what you brought.

584
00:27:40,970 --> 00:27:42,370
Steamed buns my mom made.

585
00:27:43,690 --> 00:27:44,190
Look.

586
00:27:45,270 --> 00:27:46,640
-They're still warm.
-They're really big.

587
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:48,710
I've just made some rice.

588
00:27:48,740 --> 00:27:49,870
Let's eat together.

589
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:51,160
You haven't eaten yet, have you?

590
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:52,030
Don't worry about me.

591
00:27:52,030 --> 00:27:53,160
What have you made?

592
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:00,440
Hot, hot, hot!

593
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:01,720
What is this?

594
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:02,400
Rice.

595
00:28:02,480 --> 00:28:03,440
You're just eating plain rice?

596
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:04,900
I've got some cold dishes.

597
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:10,110
Cold dishes.

598
00:28:10,780 --> 00:28:12,260
Let me get you some chopsticks.

599
00:28:12,260 --> 00:28:14,790
You're not taking care of yourself
properly.

600
00:28:21,350 --> 00:28:23,550
Here, let me do it. Don't burn yourself.

601
00:28:33,070 --> 00:28:33,750
Here.

602
00:28:37,580 --> 00:28:38,960
Have more buns.

603
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:40,220
My mom made the filling

604
00:28:40,310 --> 00:28:41,310
with lots of meat.

605
00:28:42,330 --> 00:28:44,170
This rain is on and off.

606
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:46,480
Xia Lei?

607
00:28:46,500 --> 00:28:47,230
You're here.

608
00:28:47,640 --> 00:28:48,350
Haven't eaten yet, right?

609
00:28:48,350 --> 00:28:49,510
I... I haven't eaten.

610
00:28:49,510 --> 00:28:50,680
Come on, let's eat together.

611
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:52,140
Xiaodan just got here too.

612
00:28:52,300 --> 00:28:54,910
My mom asked me to bring you some food.

613
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:56,420
Freshly made by my dad. Take a look.

614
00:28:56,420 --> 00:28:57,290
Let me see.

615
00:29:00,310 --> 00:29:01,990
This smells really delicious.

616
00:29:01,990 --> 00:29:02,920
Hurry up and eat.

617
00:29:08,310 --> 00:29:09,150
Let me. Let me.

618
00:29:09,810 --> 00:29:10,610
Xiaoman.

619
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:13,200
You want me to help you

620
00:29:13,220 --> 00:29:14,830
sort out your grandma's things?

621
00:29:14,830 --> 00:29:16,560
No need. Just leave them there.

622
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:17,350
Just leave them here?

623
00:29:17,350 --> 00:29:19,210
I feel at peace seeing them there.

624
00:29:19,420 --> 00:29:20,880
I've washed the box clean.

625
00:29:21,070 --> 00:29:24,790
Aren't you supposed to burn these for her?

626
00:29:24,960 --> 00:29:26,360
I mean... Just burn them.

627
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:27,840
I was going to,

628
00:29:27,860 --> 00:29:28,530
but then...

629
00:29:29,360 --> 00:29:30,560
I brought them back.

630
00:29:30,940 --> 00:29:32,650
Grandma used these all her life.

631
00:29:32,650 --> 00:29:33,760
Why burn them?

632
00:29:34,290 --> 00:29:36,100
Yeah, keep them if you want.

633
00:29:36,130 --> 00:29:38,360
You can look at them
when you miss your grandma.

634
00:29:38,360 --> 00:29:40,290
Where was that photo taken?

635
00:29:41,230 --> 00:29:43,630
In Shenyang, when my grandma
took me there.

636
00:29:43,690 --> 00:29:45,020
I was still little then.

637
00:29:46,290 --> 00:29:48,420
She said we'd snap one in Shenyang,

638
00:29:48,450 --> 00:29:51,410
and when I grew up,
she'd take me to Beijing

639
00:29:51,750 --> 00:29:53,280
and take one at Tian'anmen.

640
00:29:54,030 --> 00:29:55,430
But that never happened.

641
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:58,540
Your grandma looked so young in this.

642
00:30:11,670 --> 00:30:13,400
Xiaoman, setting up the stand?

643
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:16,000
Let me know if you need any help.

644
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:16,630
Work hard, alright?

645
00:30:16,630 --> 00:30:17,960
Sure thing. Sure thing.

646
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:25,400
Xiaoman, here are some apples for you.

647
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:27,400
You're too kind, Sis.

648
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:29,200
Sis, have a soda.

649
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:29,550
Sis.

650
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:30,900
No need. It's nothing.

651
00:30:34,270 --> 00:30:35,110
I'm off work.

652
00:30:35,390 --> 00:30:36,120
Ride safely.

653
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:45,370
Xiaoman.

654
00:30:45,370 --> 00:30:46,310
What do you want to buy, bro?

655
00:30:46,310 --> 00:30:47,550
Xiaoman, where did you go?

656
00:30:47,550 --> 00:30:48,400
I went to deliver newspapers.

657
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:49,030
Deliver newspapers?

658
00:30:49,030 --> 00:30:50,570
You were gone for about half an hour.

659
00:30:50,570 --> 00:30:51,840
-No, I just left.
-Have you eaten?

660
00:30:51,840 --> 00:30:52,270
Not yet.

661
00:30:52,270 --> 00:30:52,760
Hurry up.

662
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:53,260
Just in time.

663
00:30:53,260 --> 00:30:53,670
Quick.

664
00:30:54,510 --> 00:30:55,510
Come on, sit here.

665
00:30:55,930 --> 00:30:56,610
What is it?

666
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:59,310
My wife made some dumplings
this afternoon.

667
00:30:59,450 --> 00:31:00,030
Dumplings?

668
00:31:00,030 --> 00:31:01,180
She used the sauerkraut I made.

669
00:31:01,180 --> 00:31:02,680
Thin wrappers, big filling.

670
00:31:02,680 --> 00:31:03,110
I'll have a taste.

671
00:31:03,110 --> 00:31:03,610
Eat up.

672
00:31:03,630 --> 00:31:05,090
They're so good
you won't even have time to talk.

673
00:31:05,090 --> 00:31:06,000
My wife said

674
00:31:06,150 --> 00:31:07,510
they taste just like the ones
your grandma used to make.

675
00:31:07,510 --> 00:31:09,670
Taste it and see if it's the same flavor.

676
00:31:09,670 --> 00:31:11,670
Yeah, it really does taste similar.

677
00:31:13,890 --> 00:31:14,480
Well,

678
00:31:14,510 --> 00:31:16,170
I-I'm glad it tastes similar.

679
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:17,000
Then I... I...

680
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:17,790
I'll be heading back now.

681
00:31:17,790 --> 00:31:18,720
You go ahead and eat.

682
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:19,640
As for the box...

683
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:20,880
I-I'll bring it over in a bit.

684
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:21,940
Alright, alright.

685
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:25,490
I had to put my foot in it.

686
00:31:26,940 --> 00:31:27,490
Xiaoman.

687
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:28,680
By the way,

688
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:29,440
this is

689
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:31,260
the money from selling the newspapers
just now.

690
00:31:31,260 --> 00:31:31,980
I'm off.

691
00:31:32,030 --> 00:31:33,030
You sold this much in such a short time?

692
00:31:33,030 --> 00:31:34,160
Yeah, sold a ton.

693
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:55,880
Kid.

694
00:31:57,550 --> 00:31:59,660
Hop on. I'll take you for a ride.

695
00:32:07,330 --> 00:32:08,860
Who is that? Riding so fast.

696
00:32:09,980 --> 00:32:10,830
Slow down!

697
00:32:45,350 --> 00:32:46,150
Feeling good?

698
00:32:47,580 --> 00:32:48,340
Scared?

699
00:33:10,750 --> 00:33:12,880
Pretty awesome. It was really fast.

700
00:33:14,180 --> 00:33:14,730
Kid,

701
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:19,930
I've always treated you like
a younger brother.

702
00:33:19,930 --> 00:33:21,730
I think we're alike in some ways.

703
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:23,880
Life

704
00:33:25,130 --> 00:33:27,460
is full of goodbyes
we don't get to choose.

705
00:33:28,020 --> 00:33:29,480
Even if you want to hold on,

706
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:31,640
you may not be able to.

707
00:33:32,190 --> 00:33:33,460
When my dad passed away,

708
00:33:33,460 --> 00:33:35,920
Dongdong was barely
old enough to remember.

709
00:33:36,430 --> 00:33:38,290
I didn't even have time to grieve.

710
00:33:38,860 --> 00:33:40,990
I had to help my mom support the family.

711
00:33:41,370 --> 00:33:43,170
I did all kinds of work back then,

712
00:33:43,840 --> 00:33:45,030
as long as it paid.

713
00:33:54,110 --> 00:33:55,270
I'm not...

714
00:34:00,830 --> 00:34:02,510
I'm not exactly sad right now.

715
00:34:03,510 --> 00:34:04,720
I just feel...

716
00:34:08,170 --> 00:34:09,630
Feel like there's no hope.

717
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:12,679
Look, you still have a younger brother.

718
00:34:14,670 --> 00:34:16,000
With my grandma gone...

719
00:34:19,090 --> 00:34:20,550
With my grandma gone, I...

720
00:34:22,280 --> 00:34:23,150
I've got

721
00:34:23,420 --> 00:34:26,010
nothing left here.

722
00:34:28,139 --> 00:34:29,980
My dad hasn't sent word in years.

723
00:34:31,159 --> 00:34:32,760
He probably won't come back.

724
00:34:36,550 --> 00:34:37,280
Kid.

725
00:34:39,150 --> 00:34:42,210
Have you thought about
what you want to do in the future?

726
00:34:43,030 --> 00:34:44,710
Just work and make some money.

727
00:34:45,940 --> 00:34:48,400
You're a student.
What do you need money for?

728
00:34:50,190 --> 00:34:51,710
What for...

729
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:54,040
I don't know for sure.

730
00:34:54,510 --> 00:34:56,150
But having some money in my pocket

731
00:34:56,150 --> 00:34:57,550
makes me feel a bit more secure.

732
00:34:57,550 --> 00:34:58,400
Otherwise...

733
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:03,670
Secure, huh?

734
00:35:05,630 --> 00:35:06,440
Fair enough.

735
00:35:08,400 --> 00:35:11,360
If you want to make money, go ask Zhigang.

736
00:35:12,230 --> 00:35:13,630
He's got plenty of ideas.

737
00:35:15,460 --> 00:35:16,990
What else other than money?

738
00:35:18,230 --> 00:35:19,760
I haven't thought about it.

739
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:25,060
When I was a kid,
I always wanted to join the army.

740
00:35:26,120 --> 00:35:27,810
Joining the army is great.

741
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:30,000
That's really cool.

742
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:32,300
This could work.

743
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:36,380
Practice boxing with me starting today.

744
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:37,630
It'll come in handy.

745
00:35:40,670 --> 00:35:41,600
This could work.

746
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:42,500
Okay.

747
00:35:43,100 --> 00:35:44,540
[Western Tiecheng
Dongfang Affiliated Middle School]

748
00:35:44,930 --> 00:35:46,260
Come on, check this out.

749
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:48,960
See? Who would've thought he could get in?

750
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:50,840
You didn't do well. Go back and study.

751
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:52,320
-What?
-Stop crowding around here.

752
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:53,250
Xiaoman is here.

753
00:35:53,800 --> 00:35:54,400
Lulu.

754
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:56,670
Xia Lei.

755
00:35:57,440 --> 00:35:57,880
Next year,

756
00:35:57,880 --> 00:35:59,720
the top spot will definitely be yours.

757
00:35:59,720 --> 00:36:01,110
Alright, I'll try.

758
00:36:01,490 --> 00:36:03,780
[Good News]

759
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:08,120
I didn't know we could apply for
the Aviation Academy.

760
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:12,000
Pilots can join the Air Force directly.

761
00:36:12,050 --> 00:36:13,710
They recruit seniors every year.

762
00:36:13,710 --> 00:36:14,590
That's great.

763
00:36:15,530 --> 00:36:17,360
Y-You want to go?

764
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:18,920
Being a soldier is tough.

765
00:36:19,070 --> 00:36:20,190
How tough can it be?

766
00:36:20,190 --> 00:36:21,590
Worse than what I'm going through now?

767
00:36:21,590 --> 00:36:23,070
What? You want to go?

768
00:36:23,070 --> 00:36:24,000
Being a pilot.

769
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:24,880
You know,

770
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:26,340
flying airplanes.

771
00:36:26,510 --> 00:36:27,440
That's awesome.

772
00:36:27,630 --> 00:36:29,030
Flying a plane like this?

773
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:32,780
Xiaodan, what do you want to do
in the future?

774
00:36:33,190 --> 00:36:35,760
I haven't decided.
There are too many things I want to do.

775
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:37,690
True. You are Magellan, after all.

776
00:36:39,920 --> 00:36:41,290
This Magellan's first stop

777
00:36:41,290 --> 00:36:42,320
is Beijing.

778
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,660
What are you going to do in Beijing?

779
00:36:45,660 --> 00:36:47,080
There is a hosting competition in Beijing.

780
00:36:47,080 --> 00:36:48,040
I want to give it a try.

781
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:48,680
Hosting?

782
00:36:54,610 --> 00:36:56,540
You look more like you're singing.

783
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:03,590
Zhigang!

784
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:06,150
Zhigang.

785
00:37:09,550 --> 00:37:10,360
Xiaoman.

786
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:14,550
What brings you here?

787
00:37:14,550 --> 00:37:15,760
I've got nothing to do at home.

788
00:37:15,760 --> 00:37:17,600
Da said you've got work here,

789
00:37:17,710 --> 00:37:18,670
so I thought I'd come check it out

790
00:37:18,670 --> 00:37:19,550
and make some money.

791
00:37:19,550 --> 00:37:20,150
Come on up.

792
00:37:22,410 --> 00:37:24,600
Doesn't your family run a newsstand?

793
00:37:26,550 --> 00:37:27,760
Don't even get me started.

794
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:29,230
No one's bought anything for weeks.

795
00:37:29,230 --> 00:37:30,830
No one reads papers anymore.

796
00:37:31,330 --> 00:37:32,120
My goodness.

797
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:33,510
It's really

798
00:37:34,690 --> 00:37:36,950
scorching here. What are you doing here?

799
00:37:37,150 --> 00:37:38,280
Working, of course.

800
00:37:38,800 --> 00:37:39,800
What kind of work?

801
00:37:40,860 --> 00:37:42,530
Want to work with me?

802
00:37:44,070 --> 00:37:44,920
I'll show you the ropes.

803
00:37:44,920 --> 00:37:45,470
Okay.

804
00:37:47,630 --> 00:37:48,190
Zhigang.

805
00:37:49,110 --> 00:37:51,900
Seriously, what are we waiting for
in this sun?

806
00:37:53,150 --> 00:37:54,110
You'll see.

807
00:37:56,480 --> 00:37:58,940
What is it?
Why are you acting so mysterious?

808
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:11,120
Isn't that Director Hou?

809
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:12,920
Guys,

810
00:38:13,550 --> 00:38:15,320
could you help push the car?

811
00:38:15,550 --> 00:38:16,440
Director Hou!

812
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:18,510
What happened?

813
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:19,760
Zhigang!

814
00:38:20,480 --> 00:38:21,210
Just in time.

815
00:38:21,870 --> 00:38:23,060
I need a favor.

816
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:25,370
Please lend me a hand
and give the car a push.

817
00:38:25,370 --> 00:38:26,590
You need our help, right?

818
00:38:26,590 --> 00:38:27,510
Yes, yes.

819
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:28,620
Sure thing.

820
00:38:29,630 --> 00:38:30,560
Here comes work.

821
00:38:32,470 --> 00:38:33,280
Come on, guys.

822
00:38:34,780 --> 00:38:35,340
Let's go.

823
00:38:36,760 --> 00:38:37,590
Director Hou!

824
00:38:38,320 --> 00:38:39,670
Nice car.

825
00:38:40,670 --> 00:38:41,360
Look at this car.

826
00:38:41,360 --> 00:38:42,560
What's nice about it?

827
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:44,030
It belongs to the state—

828
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:45,290
no good or bad about it.

829
00:38:46,070 --> 00:38:46,670
Zhigang.

830
00:38:47,550 --> 00:38:48,720
Do me a favor.

831
00:38:48,740 --> 00:38:49,980
Ask your buddies

832
00:38:50,010 --> 00:38:50,940
to help push it.

833
00:38:56,960 --> 00:38:57,820
You want money?

834
00:38:58,630 --> 00:38:59,480
Of course.

835
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:00,480
Look,

836
00:39:00,480 --> 00:39:01,030
we're out here

837
00:39:01,030 --> 00:39:01,630
in the wind and sun.

838
00:39:01,630 --> 00:39:02,960
We deserve a little
hard-earned pay, right?

839
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:03,890
Don't you agree?

840
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:12,270
Hit the gas.
I don't believe we can't get out.

841
00:39:12,270 --> 00:39:13,000
Sure, hit it.

842
00:39:13,900 --> 00:39:14,470
Come on.

843
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:16,890
Floor it!

844
00:39:23,480 --> 00:39:24,600
How can they possibly get out?

845
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:26,730
Right, sir. This way! This way. Right.

846
00:39:27,590 --> 00:39:28,960
Turn the wheel right!

847
00:39:31,920 --> 00:39:33,000
Alright, fine.

848
00:39:35,430 --> 00:39:37,620
Zhigang, how about this?

849
00:39:38,590 --> 00:39:39,850
Thirty yuan, alright?

850
00:39:40,380 --> 00:39:42,510
This kind of cost isn't reimbursable,

851
00:39:42,720 --> 00:39:44,650
so I have to pay out of my own pocket.

852
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:45,600
Director Hou,

853
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:48,960
if it were anyone else,

854
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:50,230
I'd charge 30.

855
00:39:50,590 --> 00:39:52,450
But since it's you, Director Hou,

856
00:39:52,880 --> 00:39:54,140
I'll have to charge 50.

857
00:40:01,670 --> 00:40:03,070
Thank you, Director Hou.

858
00:40:03,170 --> 00:40:04,840
Come on, guys. Let's get to work!

859
00:40:04,840 --> 00:40:05,550
Hurry up.

860
00:40:07,180 --> 00:40:07,980
Come on.

861
00:40:18,110 --> 00:40:19,440
Bye-bye, Director Hou.

862
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:24,480
Xiaoman.

863
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:29,990
Zhigang.

864
00:40:31,840 --> 00:40:33,000
Fifty to push a car?

865
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,530
Isn't that a bit expensive?

866
00:40:35,230 --> 00:40:36,360
We're all working out in the sun and wind,

867
00:40:36,360 --> 00:40:38,960
making some hard-earned money.

868
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:40,630
It's almost like you're barefoot,

869
00:40:40,630 --> 00:40:42,960
yet you worry about sand in others' shoes.

870
00:40:46,270 --> 00:40:47,470
Come on, back to work.

871
00:40:48,030 --> 00:40:48,840
Coming.

872
00:40:53,630 --> 00:40:56,360
You guys, pour a few more
buckets of water in there!

873
00:40:56,360 --> 00:40:57,070
Got it.

874
00:40:57,990 --> 00:40:58,960
Mix it evenly!

875
00:41:03,280 --> 00:41:04,030
Zhigang.

876
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:09,210
If we keep digging holes like this,

877
00:41:09,710 --> 00:41:11,310
isn't that basically a scam?

878
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:12,550
What scam?

879
00:41:13,280 --> 00:41:13,730
I'm telling you,

880
00:41:13,730 --> 00:41:15,190
these people with cars nowadays—

881
00:41:15,190 --> 00:41:17,390
how many of them got their money fairly?

882
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:19,400
But

883
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:22,730
the cars on this road
are mostly from the factory.

884
00:41:23,480 --> 00:41:24,920
So what if they're from the factory?

885
00:41:24,920 --> 00:41:27,070
I'm precisely targeting the factory cars.

886
00:41:27,070 --> 00:41:28,800
I didn't even get my quarterly bonus.

887
00:41:28,800 --> 00:41:30,000
So shouldn't I level the playing field

888
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:31,460
with the factory leaders?

889
00:41:34,070 --> 00:41:35,730
After my grandma passed away,

890
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:38,120
those in the factory
really took care of me.

891
00:41:38,120 --> 00:41:39,320
They treated me well.

892
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:41,080
So how can I scam the factory?

893
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:44,030
Let me tell you,
your mindset is problematic.

894
00:41:44,030 --> 00:41:45,110
Your way of thinking is wrong,

895
00:41:45,110 --> 00:41:45,670
you know?

896
00:41:45,670 --> 00:41:46,910
Do you think

897
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:49,360
making money nowadays is that easy?

898
00:41:49,360 --> 00:41:51,800
You think you can still earn it
by following the rules?

899
00:41:51,800 --> 00:41:52,320
The factory?

900
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:53,590
Look at what the factory has done to us.

901
00:41:53,590 --> 00:41:54,360
And you're still trying to defend it?

902
00:41:54,360 --> 00:41:55,360
I don't want to do this.

903
00:41:55,360 --> 00:41:56,480
Look at the state you're in now.

904
00:41:56,480 --> 00:41:58,070
You're still thinking about
not scamming them?

905
00:41:58,070 --> 00:41:59,870
Hasn't the factory scammed you?

906
00:42:02,630 --> 00:42:03,610
We've got business.

907
00:42:03,610 --> 00:42:05,410
-Come on.
-You go. I'm not going.

908
00:42:21,010 --> 00:42:21,860
Mr. Yan.

909
00:42:22,690 --> 00:42:23,520
What happened?

910
00:42:23,520 --> 00:42:24,750
It's you guys.

911
00:42:25,590 --> 00:42:27,390
Your car's stuck here, isn't it?

912
00:42:27,510 --> 00:42:28,480
Do you need help?

913
00:42:28,580 --> 00:42:29,060
Yes.

914
00:42:29,080 --> 00:42:30,940
Since you're here, give it a push.

915
00:42:32,520 --> 00:42:33,450
What do you mean?

916
00:42:38,280 --> 00:42:40,030
Mr. Yan, you see,
you want us to help you out,

917
00:42:40,030 --> 00:42:42,090
but we can't do it for nothing, right?

918
00:42:42,480 --> 00:42:43,070
Fine.

919
00:42:43,320 --> 00:42:44,670
I'll pay. It's okay.

920
00:42:44,670 --> 00:42:46,110
G-Go buy some bottles of soda, alright?

921
00:42:46,110 --> 00:42:48,000
We're Xiaodan's good friends.

922
00:42:48,670 --> 00:42:49,530
We'll help you.

923
00:42:49,580 --> 00:42:50,100
Okay?

924
00:42:50,340 --> 00:42:52,130
Alright, alright. Thank you.

925
00:42:52,370 --> 00:42:53,000
Xiaoman!

926
00:42:54,110 --> 00:42:55,800
Xiaoman, come and help!

927
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:57,590
Xiaoman!

928
00:42:58,120 --> 00:42:59,080
Come and help!

929
00:43:00,800 --> 00:43:01,670
Come on!
